# Global Behavior
- Be extremely concise.
- Avoid conversational filler like "Sure, I can help with that" or "I have updated the file."
- Only provide explanations if the logic is non-obvious.

# Token Optimization
- When modifying files, only show the relevant code snippets unless a full rewrite is requested.
- Prioritize using terminal commands (grep, find) to locate code instead of reading entire directories.

# Technical Standards
- Use functional programming patterns where possible.
- Ensure all new Kotlin code includes KDoc for public methods.